We need to identify the initial capital injection transactions. In this case the “Initial20231231001” lines contain three transactions:
• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.0

Adding these amounts gives the paid‐in capital:
  3,000,000 + 5,000,000 + 8,000,000 = 16,000,000

Since no transactions after the initial injections adjust the paid‑in capital, both the initial and the end value remain the same.

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "16000000.00",
    "Paid-in Capital End Value": "16000000.00"
  }
}
